"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:11.3.1.5\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">11.3.1.5</span> Kor</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">כֹּר</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(kor)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:2\">1KI 5:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:2\">1KI 5:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:25\">1KI 5:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:25\">1KI 5:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:9\">2CH 2:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:9\">2CH 2:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr27:5\">2CH 27:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:14\">EZK 45:14</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Aramaic</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">כֹּר</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(kor)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra7:22\">EZR 7:22</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">According to <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:14\">EZK 45:14</a>, the <em>kor</em> is the same as the <em>chomer</em>.</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:25\">1KI 5:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:25\">1KI 5:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:9\">2CH 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:9\">2CH 2:9</a>: The amount of oil which Solomon provides to Hiram is different by a factor of one hundred between these two verses. <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:25\">1KI 5:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:25\">1KI 5:25</a> has “20 cors,” while the parallel text in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:9\">2CH 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:9\">2CH 2:9</a> has “20,000 baths.” <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Hebrew Old Testament Text Project (UBS)\">HOTTP</abbr> accepts “twenty cors” as the best reading at <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:25\">1KI 5:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:25\">1KI 5:25</a> and remarks that the translator should resist the temptation to harmonize the two texts. Not all commentators and translations agree with <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Hebrew Old Testament Text Project (UBS)\">HOTTP</abbr> ’s reading, however, and some prefer to accept the Septuagint’s “20,000 baths,” which brings the two texts into line.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
